# Content Schema & Validation

Single source of truth for all content collections, their Zod schemas, relationships, draft system, helpers, and build-time validation.

---

## Config Location

`src/content.config.ts` (at root of `src/`, not `src/content/`). Both paths work in Astro v5+, but this project uses the root path.

---

## Content Loader

All collections use a shared `contentLoader()` that centralizes glob patterns, ID generation, and draft filtering:

```ts
import { defineCollection, reference, z } from "astro:content";
import { glob, type Loader } from "astro/loaders";

const contentLoader = ({ base, extensions }: { extensions: string[]; base: string }): Loader => {
  const stripExtension = ({ entry }: { entry: string }) => {
    return entry.replace(/\.(mdx?|yaml)$/, "");
  };

  // In development: include all files (drafts visible for preview)
  // In production: exclude *.draft.* files at the glob level
  const draftFilter = import.meta.env.MODE === "development" ? "**" : "!(*.draft)";
  const extensionFilter = extensions.length > 1 ? `{${extensions.join(",")}}` : extensions[0];

  return glob({
    pattern: `**/${draftFilter}.${extensionFilter}`,
    base,
    generateId: stripExtension,
  });
};
```

Key behaviors:
- **Dev** (`pnpm dev`): all files loaded, including `*.draft.*`
- **Prod** (`pnpm build`): `*.draft.*` excluded at the glob level, never enters the content layer
- **ID generation**: strips file extensions for clean URL slugs (`example-project.mdx` -> `example-project`)
- Draft filtering happens at loader level, not query-time. No filtering needed in `getCollection()` calls.

---

## Shared Schemas

```ts
const seoSchema = z.object({
  metaTitle: z.string().optional(),
  metaDescription: z.string().optional(),
  ogImage: z.string().optional(),
});

const metricSchema = z.object({
  value: z.string(),
  label: z.string(),
});
```

---

## Collections

### Projects (MDX)

```ts
const projects = defineCollection({
  loader: contentLoader({
    base: "src/content/projects",
    extensions: ["mdx"],
  }),
  schema: z.object({
    title: z.string(),
    tagline: z.string().optional(),
    client: z.string().optional(),
    date: z.coerce.date(),
    thumbnail: z.string(),
    heroImage: z.string().optional(),
    tags: z.array(z.string()).default([]),
    industry: z.array(z.string()).default([]),
    deliverable: z.array(z.string()).default([]),
    metrics: z.array(metricSchema).default([]),
    seo: seoSchema.optional(),
    relatedProjects: z.array(reference("projects")).default([]),
  }),
});
```

| Field | Notes |
|---|---|
| `thumbnail` | CDN path for listing cards (required) |
| `heroImage` | CDN path for homepage showcase and project detail header |
| `industry` | Categories for filtering (e.g. "fintech", "e-commerce", "healthcare") |
| `deliverable` | Types for filtering (e.g. "website", "mobile-app", "design-system") |
| `metrics` | Shown on project cards (e.g. `{ value: "55%+", label: "Conversion" }`) |
| `relatedProjects` | Build-time validated slugs of related projects |

### Blog (MD/MDX)

Supports both `.md` (no components) and `.mdx` (with components).

```ts
const blog = defineCollection({
  loader: contentLoader({
    extensions: ["md", "mdx"],
    base: "src/content/blog",
  }),
  schema: z.object({
    title: z.string(),
    description: z.string().optional(),
    date: z.coerce.date(),
    author: z.string().optional(),
    thumbnail: z.string().optional(),
    tags: z.array(z.string()).default([]),
    seo: seoSchema.optional(),
    relatedProjects: z.array(reference("projects")).default([]),
  }),
});
```

### Playground (MD/MDX)

Open source projects and experiments.

```ts
const playground = defineCollection({
  loader: contentLoader({
    extensions: ["md", "mdx"],
    base: "src/content/playground",
  }),
  schema: z.object({
    title: z.string(),
    description: z.string(),
    date: z.coerce.date(),
    repoUrl: z.string().url().optional(),
    thumbnail: z.string().optional(),
    tags: z.array(z.string()).default([]),
    seo: seoSchema.optional(),
  }),
});
```

### Pages (MDX)

Miscellaneous content pages (about, services, etc.) rendered by `[...slug].astro`.

```ts
const pages = defineCollection({
  loader: contentLoader({
    extensions: ["mdx"],
    base: "src/content/pages",
  }),
  schema: z.object({
    title: z.string(),
    seo: seoSchema.optional(),
  }),
});
```

### Highlights (YAML)

Homepage curation. Each entry references an item in another collection via discriminated union. Astro validates every slug at build time.

```ts
const highlights = defineCollection({
  loader: contentLoader({
    extensions: ["yaml"],
    base: "src/content/highlights",
  }),
  schema: z.object({
    label: z.string().optional(),
    source: z.discriminatedUnion("collection", [
      z.object({ collection: z.literal("projects"), entry: reference("projects") }),
      z.object({ collection: z.literal("blog"), entry: reference("blog") }),
      z.object({ collection: z.literal("playground"), entry: reference("playground") }),
    ]),
    order: z.number(),
  }),
});
```

Example YAML:

```yaml
# src/content/highlights/01-cool-project.yaml
order: 1
label: Featured Project
source:
  collection: projects
  entry: example-project
```

If `example-project` doesn't exist in `src/content/projects/`, the build fails. If the referenced file is a draft, it works in dev but fails the production build.

### Clients (YAML)

```ts
const clients = defineCollection({
  loader: contentLoader({
    extensions: ["yaml"],
    base: "src/content/clients",
  }),
  schema: z.object({
    name: z.string(),
    logo: z.string(),
    url: z.string().url().optional(),
    order: z.number().default(0),
  }),
});
```

| Field | Notes |
|---|---|
| `logo` | Path to SVG logo in `public/` (e.g. `/logos/boeing.svg`) |
| `order` | Sort order ascending. Default `0` |

### Testimonials (YAML)

```ts
const testimonials = defineCollection({
  loader: contentLoader({
    extensions: ["yaml"],
    base: "src/content/testimonials",
  }),
  schema: z.object({
    quote: z.string(),
    author: z.string(),
    role: z.string(),
    company: z.string(),
    avatar: z.string().optional(),
    order: z.number().default(0),
  }),
});
```

| Field | Notes |
|---|---|
| `avatar` | CDN path to author photo |

### Awards (YAML)

```ts
const awards = defineCollection({
  loader: contentLoader({
    extensions: ["yaml"],
    base: "src/content/awards",
  }),
  schema: z.object({
    award: z.string(),
    year: z.number(),
    project: reference("projects"),
    url: z.string().url().optional(),
    order: z.number().default(0),
  }),
});
```

| Field | Notes |
|---|---|
| `project` | Project that won the award. Build-time validated reference. |

### Handbook Groups (YAML)

Visual categories shown on the handbook index page. Filenames act as slugs referenced by handbook pages (e.g. `engineering.yaml` -> `group: engineering`).

```ts
const handbookGroups = defineCollection({
  loader: contentLoader({
    extensions: ["yaml"],
    base: "src/content/handbook-groups",
  }),
  schema: z.object({
    title: z.string(),
    order: z.number(),
  }),
});
```

### Handbook (MDX)

Internal company docs. File path determines both URL and parent-child hierarchy.

```ts
const handbook = defineCollection({
  loader: contentLoader({
    extensions: ["mdx"],
    base: "src/content/handbook",
  }),
  schema: z.object({
    title: z.string(),
    description: z.string().optional(),
    date: z.coerce.date(),
    coverImage: z.string().optional(),
    group: reference("handbook-groups"),
    order: z.number().default(0),
    seo: seoSchema.optional(),
  }),
});
```

**File structure determines hierarchy:**

```
src/content/handbook/
  culture.mdx                            -> /handbook/culture          (top-level)
  how-we-build-software.mdx              -> /handbook/how-we-build-software  (parent)
  how-we-build-software/
    front-end-development.mdx            -> /handbook/how-we-build-software/front-end-development
    back-end-development.mdx             -> /handbook/how-we-build-software/back-end-development
```

- A page becomes a parent when a sibling directory shares its name and contains MDX files.
- Children inherit their parent's URL as a prefix.
- Nesting beyond one level is supported but should be used sparingly.
- The `group` field is required on child pages too (controls sidebar navigation).
- `coverImage` is a CDN path displayed at the top of the page.

---

## Export Block

All collections must be exported from `src/content.config.ts`:

```ts
export const collections = {
  projects,
  blog,
  playground,
  pages,
  highlights,
  clients,
  testimonials,
  awards,
  "handbook-groups": handbookGroups,
  handbook,
};
```

---

## Draft System

Drafts use the `.draft` filename suffix, not a frontmatter field. Do not use a `draft` boolean in frontmatter.

| File | Dev (`pnpm dev`) | Prod (`pnpm build`) |
|---|---|---|
| `cool-project.mdx` | Loaded | Loaded |
| `cool-project.draft.mdx` | Loaded (preview) | Excluded at glob level |

**Workflow:**
1. Create a draft: name it `my-post.draft.mdx` (or `.draft.md`, `.draft.yaml`)
2. Preview locally: `pnpm dev` includes drafts in the content layer
3. Publish: rename `my-post.draft.mdx` -> `my-post.mdx`
4. Unpublish: rename back

**References to drafts:** If a non-draft entry (highlight, award) references a draft entry, it works in dev but fails the production build because the draft is excluded from the collection. This prevents shipping pages that link to unpublished content.

---

## Relationships

All cross-content references use `reference()` for build-time validation. `reference()` returns `{ id, collection }` objects, not full entries. Resolve with `getEntry()`.

### Pattern 1: Related Projects in a Case Study

Frontmatter in `src/content/projects/cool-project.mdx`:

```yaml
relatedProjects:
  - another-project
  - third-project
```

Resolved in template:

```ts
const relatedProjects = project.data.relatedProjects?.length
  ? await Promise.all(project.data.relatedProjects.map((ref) => getEntry(ref)))
  : [];
```

If `another-project` or `third-project` don't exist as files, the build fails immediately.

### Pattern 2: Homepage Highlights (Cross-Collection)

Each highlight references an entry in another collection via `discriminatedUnion`. Resolved in `src/lib/collections.ts`:

```ts
export async function getResolvedHighlights() {
  const allHighlights = await getCollection("highlights");
  const sorted = allHighlights.sort((a, b) => a.data.order - b.data.order);

  const resolved = await Promise.all(
    sorted.map(async (h) => {
      const entry = await getEntry(h.data.source.collection, h.data.source.entry.id);
      return {
        label: h.data.label,
        collection: h.data.source.collection,
        entry,
      };
    })
  );

  return resolved;
}
```

### Pattern 3: Awards with Project References

```ts
export async function getAwards() {
  const allAwards = await getCollection("awards");
  const sorted = allAwards.sort((a, b) => a.data.order - b.data.order);

  const resolved = await Promise.all(
    sorted.map(async (a) => {
      const project = await getEntry("projects", a.data.project.id);
      return {
        award: a.data.award,
        year: a.data.year,
        url: a.data.url,
        project,
      };
    })
  );

  return resolved;
}
```

### Pattern 4: MDX Cross-Sell Component

Inside any `.mdx` file:

```mdx
<ProjectCrossSell slug="another-project" />
```

The component resolves the slug with `getEntry()` and throws at build time if not found.

---

## Helper Functions

All in `src/lib/collections.ts`. No draft filtering needed since the loader handles it.

| Function | Returns |
|---|---|
| `getProjects()` | All projects, sorted by date desc |
| `getPosts()` | All blog posts, sorted by date desc |
| `getPlayground()` | All playground entries, sorted by date desc |
| `getClients()` | All clients, sorted by order asc |
| `getTestimonials()` | All testimonials, sorted by order asc |
| `getResolvedHighlights()` | Highlights with referenced entries resolved |
| `getAwards()` | Awards with referenced projects resolved |
| `getHandbookGroups()` | All handbook groups, sorted by order asc |
| `getHandbookPages()` | All handbook pages, sorted by order asc |
| `getTopLevelHandbookPages()` | Handbook pages without a parent (no `/` in ID) |
| `getHandbookChildren(parentId)` | Direct children of a handbook page |
| `getHandbookParent(entry)` | Parent entry for a handbook page, or null |
| `getHandbookBreadcrumbs(entry)` | Ancestor chain from root to the current page |
| `getHandbookIndex()` | Full grouped structure for the index page |

**Types:** `HandbookEntry` and `HandbookGroupEntry` are exported as `CollectionEntry<"handbook">` and `CollectionEntry<"handbook-groups">`.

---

## Build-Time Validation

### Slug Collision Check

The catch-all `[...slug].astro` validates that no page slug collides with reserved routes:

```ts
// In src/pages/[...slug].astro getStaticPaths()
const reserved = ["blog", "projects", "labs", "handbook", "who-we-are", "what-we-do", "work-with-us"];

for (const page of pages) {
  const topSegment = page.id.split("/")[0];
  if (reserved.includes(topSegment)) {
    throw new Error(`Page "${page.id}" collides with reserved route /${topSegment}. Rename it.`);
  }
}
```

### Content Error Helper

`src/lib/content-errors.ts` wraps build-time errors with actionable context:

```ts
export function contentError(component: string, file: string, message: string): never {
  throw new Error(`[${component}] in ${file}: ${message}\nFix the content and rebuild.`);
}
```

### Why `reference()` Over Plain Slugs

Always use `reference()` instead of `z.string()` for cross-collection links:
- Build fails immediately on broken references
- Non-technical content editors get instant feedback
- No runtime errors reach production

---

## Common Mistakes

1. **Using `import.meta.glob` instead of Content Collections.** Use `getCollection()` and `getEntry()` from `astro:content`.
2. **Forgetting async.** Always `await` your `getCollection()` and `getEntry()` calls.
3. **Putting content in `src/pages/` instead of `src/content/`.** Pages are routes. Content is data.
4. **Expecting `reference()` to return full entries.** It returns `{ id, collection }` stubs. Resolve with `getEntry(ref)`.
5. **MDX components aren't auto-available.** Pass them explicitly via the `components` prop when rendering. Registered in `src/components/mdx/components.ts`.
6. **Referencing a draft from non-draft content.** If a highlight or award references a `.draft` project, dev works fine but `pnpm build` fails because the draft is excluded from the collection.
7. **Catch-all route collision.** If a page in `src/content/pages/` has a slug matching a reserved route (`blog`, `projects`, etc.), the build-time check throws.
8. **Using `getStaticPaths` for non-dynamic routes.** Only `[slug].astro` and `[...slug].astro` files need it. Static pages like `index.astro` call `getCollection()` directly.
9. **Using a `draft` frontmatter field.** Drafts are filename-based (`.draft` suffix), not schema-based. The content loader handles filtering automatically.
10. **Using `fetch()` to load content.** This is a static site. All content comes from Content Collections at build time.
11. **Static paths must be exhaustive.** Every URL must be returned by `getStaticPaths()`. Missing = 404.
